==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synoptist
<hw>Syn*op"tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any one of the
authors of the three synoptic Gospels, which give a history of our
Lord's life and ministry, in distinction from the writer of John's
Gospel, which gives a fuller record of his teachings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synosteology</ent>⟦br⟧
